The 28-year-old was found hanging from a tree in a Roodepoort veld on Monday after she went missing last week. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police say they are doing everything they can to find Tshegofatso Pule's murderer. Gauteng police spokesperson Kay Makhubele says they are relying on information from the public to crack the Pule case. The heavily pregnant woman was found stabbed and hanged in Roodepoort last week. "The information which the community is giving us is what we are following up. We believe if they continue to give the information, we are going to make arrests." READ: Femicide in the spotlight South Africa Pule's death is one of several murders of women in the country recently and has lead to calls for the government to do more about South Africa's femicide crisis.